rsgain
------------------------------------------
rsgain (really simple gain) is a ReplayGain 2.0 command line utility for
Windows, macOS, Linux, BSD, and Android. rsgain applies loudness metadata tags
to your files, while leaving the audio stream untouched. A
ReplayGain-compatible player will dynamically adjust the volume of your tagged
files during playback.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libavcodec62-8.1.1-3
  libavformat62-8.1.1-3
  libavutil60-8.1.1-3
  libebur128_1-1.2.6-1bl2
  libfmt12-12.1.0-1bl1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libinih0-57-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  libswresample6-8.1.1-3
  libtag2-2.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libavcodec-devel-8.1.1-3
  libavformat-devel-8.1.1-3
  libavutil-devel-8.1.1-3
  libebur128-devel-1.2.6-1bl2
  libfmt-devel-12.1.0-1bl1
  libinih-devel-57-1
  libswresample-devel-8.1.1-3
  libtag-devel-2.3-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/complexlogic/rsgain

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/complexlogic/rsgain/archive/refs/tags/v3.7.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rsgain-3.7-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rsgain-3.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rsgain-3.7-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rsgain-3.7-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

